{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Cocaine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_harmfulness#/media/File:HarmCausedByDrugsTable.svg) is less harmful than alcohol, and only slightly more addictive. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would be more difficult to use to drugs as a mean of coercion if there would be legal ways of obtaining them and no need to hide the use of narcotics as it would no longer be illegal. {'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Ketamine](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322534.php?iacp), a promising alternative to opioids, is currently banned. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mexico](https://www.globalresearch.ca/destabilizing-mexico/12707) has been destabilized by drug cartel activities such as lawlessness, kidnappings, increasing corruption and frequent assassinations.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Aquiring drugs in a legal setting allows for regulation that may require informing the buyer about dangerous combinations, or avoid selling to people already under the influence of other drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The risk of MDMA is not higher than many sports. MDMA has been compared to [horseback riding](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk/7876425.stm) in terms of risks. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Or it suggests that by removing the profit motive of banned drugs, the suppliers were less motivated to produce and distribute it.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tobacco farming before abolition was [done by slaves](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_in_the_American_colonies). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, there were very few production standards \\(if any\\), meaning the consumer did not know what \\(potentially dangerous\\) conditions the alcohol had been manufactured in \\([pg. 4](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalization improves government finances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
